Data is downloaded for 2000 and 2010 censuses. The variables and their levels are coded as they are on IPUMS-I documentation. Finally, the data is joined to the ethnic block classifications.

data_joined <- data %>% filter(YEAR %in% c(2000, 2010))

for (var in names(data_joined)[!endsWith(names(data_joined), "LOC")]) {
  tryCatch({
    list <- list()
    list[["names"]] <- names(attr(data_joined[[var]], "labels"))
    list[["keys"]] <- as.numeric(attr(data_joined[[var]], "labels"))

    
    data_joined[[var]] <- ifelse(
      data_joined[[var]] %in% list[["keys"]],
      list[["names"]][
        match(data_joined[[var]], list[["keys"]])
      ],
      data_joined[[var]]
    )

    #cat("FINISHED", var, "\n")
  },  error = function(e) {
    cat("ERROR in variable", var, ": ", e$message, "\n")
  })
}

data_joined <- data_joined %>%
  mutate(
    Married = as.integer(MarriageStatus == "Married/in union"),
    PlausiblyMarried = as.integer(MarriageStatus == "Married/in union" |
      (SpouseID != 0 &
      !is.na(SpouseID) &
      MarriageStatus == "NIU (not in universe)" &
      grepl("couple adjacent", SpouseRule))
      )
    )

data_joined <- data_joined %>%
  mutate(
    Age = case_when(
      Age == "1 year" ~ "1",
      Age == "2 years" ~ "2",
      Age == "Less than 1 year" ~ "0",
      TRUE ~ Age
    )
  ) %>%
  mutate(Age = as.integer(Age))

data_joined <- data_joined %>%
  mutate(
    MigYrs = case_when(
      MigYrs == "1 year (or 1 year or less)" ~ "1",
      MigYrs == "Less than 1 year" ~ "1",
      MigYrs == "2 years" ~ "2",
      MigYrs == "NIU (not in universe)" ~ NA,
      TRUE ~ MigYrs
    )
  ) %>%
  mutate(MigYrs = as.integer(MigYrs))

data_joined <- data_joined %>%
  mutate(AgeMarried = case_when(
    AgeMarried == "NIU (not in universe)" ~ NA,
    TRUE ~ AgeMarried
  ))

marriages <- data_joined %>%
  group_by(YearHousehold) %>%
  filter(Sex == "Male", Married == TRUE) %>%
  inner_join(data_joined,
    by = c("YearHousehold", "SpouseID" = "PersonID"),
    suffix = c("_M", "_F")
    ) %>%
  rename(SpouseID_M = PersonID)

all(marriages$SpouseID_M == marriages$SpouseID_F) # all matched
[1] TRUE
all(marriages$Sex_M != marriages$Sex_F) # all same-sex
[1] TRUE
marriages <- marriages %>%
  select(
    YearHousehold, SpouseID_M, SpouseID_F,
    Strata = Strata_M,
    CensusYear = CensusYear_M,
    Urban = Urban_M,

I match people with their spouses by year and household, leading to 298,153 (conservative) or 309,798 (NIU included) couples. With the more conservative marriage rule, 3,815 people have more than one wife. With the inclusion of NIU entries, there are 4,049.

marriages <- marriages %>%
  mutate(
    AgeMarried_F = case_when(
      is.na(AgeMarried_F) ~ 19,
      TRUE ~ AgeMarried_F
    ),
    AgeMarried_M = case_when(
      is.na(AgeMarried_M) ~ 25,
      TRUE ~ AgeMarried_M
    ),
    YearMarried = CensusYear - (Age_F - AgeMarried_F),
    YearsMarried = Age_F - AgeMarried_F
  )

The mean ages at marriage are 19 for women and 25 for men, which serve as the imputation for missing values.

Problem: some people are under 19, meaning the year of marriage is in the future. E.g. for census 2010, a couple where both are 18 would be coded as being married in 2011.

urban_rural <- data_joined %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  filter(CensusYear == 2000) %>%
  select(CensusYear, Const, Strata, Urban) %>%
  group_by(Const, Strata, Urban) %>%
  mutate(Urban = case_when(Urban == "Urban" ~ "1", Urban == "Rural" ~ "0", TRUE ~ Urban)) %>%
  mutate(Urban = as.integer(Urban)) %>%
  distinct() %>%
  left_join(data_joined %>% 
    filter(CensusYear == 2000) %>%
    group_by(Strata) %>%
    summarise(count = n()), by = "Strata") %>%
  group_by(Const) %>%
  summarise(
    UrbanCount = sum(Urban * count), 
    Population = sum(count)
  ) %>%
  mutate(Urbanization = UrbanCount / Population)

urban_rural <- urban_rural %>% select(Const, Urbanization)

Every repeated strata is located within the same constituency. Some stratas have two classifications, for unknown reasons. I aggregate the average urbanization rate and adjust by the population of each strata. The five number summary of the urbanization rates is:

[0.00000000, 0.00000000, 0.08179886, 0.36896646, 1.00000000]

marriages <- marriages %>%
  mutate(
    EthnicOutmarriage = case_when(
      Ethnicity_M != Ethnicity_F ~ 1,
      Ethnicity_M == Ethnicity_F ~ 0,
      TRUE ~ NA),
    BlockOutmarriage = case_when(
      EthnicBlock_M != EthnicBlock_F ~ 1,
      EthnicBlock_M == EthnicBlock_F ~ 0,
      TRUE ~ NA),
    FullReside = ifelse(
      (Age_F - AgeMarried_F <= MigYrs_F) &
        (Age_M - AgeMarried_M <= MigYrs_M),
        1, 0),
    Decade = cut(YearMarried, breaks = seq(1921, 2011, by = 10),
      right = FALSE,
      labels = paste(seq(1921, 2001, by = 10),
        seq(1930, 2010, by = 10), sep = "-"))
    )

ethnic_proportions <- over_18 %>%
  group_by(Const, Ethnicity) %>%
  filter(Ethnicity != "Drop") %>%
  summarise(n = n(), .groups = "keep") %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  group_by(Const) %>%
  mutate(Proportion = n / sum(n)) %>%
  select(-n)

const_hhi <- ethnic_proportions %>%
  group_by(Const) %>%
  summarise(hhi = sum((Proportion)^2))

write.csv(ethnic_proportions, "exports/ethnic_proportions.csv")
write.csv(const_hhi, "exports/ethnicity_const_hhi.csv")

correct_geo_labels <- data_joined %>%
  select(CensusYear, Const, District, Province) %>%
  distinct()

correct_geo_labels <- correct_geo_labels %>%
  mutate(
    NewProvince = case_when(
      CensusYear == 2010 &
        District %in% c("Chama", "Chinsali", "Isoka, Mafinga, Nakonde") ~ "Muchinga",
      District %in% c("Chavuma, Zambezi", "Kabompo", "Kasempa",
          "Mufumbwe", "Solwezi", "Ikelenge, Mwinilunga") ~ "Northwestern",
      TRUE ~ Province
    )
  )

  by = join_by(CensusYear, Const, District))
